User Stories:

1. User Registration and Profile Management:
  ● As a new user, I want to be able to create an account on the platform.
  ● Acceptance Criteria:
    ○ Users can sign up using an email address and password.
    ○ Users must verify their email address to complete the registration process.
    ○ Users can optionally sign up using social media accounts (e.g., Google, Facebook).
  ● As a registered user, I want to be able to manage my profile and preferences.
  ● Acceptance Criteria:
    ○ Users can edit their profile information, including name, email, and password.
    ○ Users can specify their travel interests, budget, and accommodation preferences.
    ○ Changes to the profile are saved and reflected across the platform.

2. Personalized Recommendations:
  ● As a user, I want to receive personalized recommendations for destinations, accommodations, activities, and transportation options based on my preferences.
  ● Acceptance Criteria:
    ○ The platform analyzes user preferences using AI algorithms.
    ○ Recommendations are displayed on the homepage or in a dedicated recommendations section.
    ○ Users can provide feedback on recommendations to improve future suggestions.

3. Advanced Search and Filtering:
  ● As a user, I want to be able to search and filter travel options based on various criteria.
  ● Acceptance Criteria:
    ○ Users can search for destinations, accommodations, activities, and transportation options.
    ○ Filtering options include location, price range, ratings, amenities, and user preferences.
    ○ Search results are displayed accurately and updated in real-time as filters are applied.

4. Itinerary Planning:
  ● As a user, I want to create and manage comprehensive travel itineraries.
  ● Acceptance Criteria:
    ○ Users can add flights, accommodations, activities, and transportation options to their itinerary.
    ○ Itineraries can be customized and optimized according to user preferences.
    ○ Users can view and edit their itineraries, including adding or removing items and adjusting dates and times.

5. Real-time Updates and Notifications:
  ● As a user, I want to receive real-time updates on my bookings, flight status, and personalized recommendations.
  ● Acceptance Criteria:
    ○ Users receive push notifications, email alerts, or in-app notifications for booking confirmations, flight status changes, travel advisories, and
      personalized recommendations.
    ○ Notifications are delivered promptly and accurately.

6. Feedback and Review System:
  ● As a user, I want to leave reviews and ratings for accommodations, activities, and services.
  ● Acceptance Criteria:
    ○ Users can leave reviews and ratings for each booked item.
    ○ Reviews are displayed publicly along with the corresponding items.
    ○ The platform uses user feedback to improve recommendations and enhance the overall quality of the platform.

7. Responsive Design:
  ● As a user, I want the platform to be responsive and compatible with various devices and screen sizes.
  ● Acceptance Criteria:
    ○ The platform is accessible and functional on desktops, laptops, tablets, and smartphones.
    ○ Content and layout adapt seamlessly to different screen sizes and orientations.
    ○ Users can navigate and interact with the platform comfortably on any device.

8. Finalizing Language Model for Itinerary Planning
  ● As a developer, I want to efficiently finalize the Language Model (LLM) to be used in itinerary planning by thoroughly 
    testing various options and selecting the most suitable one based on defined criteria.
  ● Acceptance Criteria:
    ○ Evaluate and compare multiple language models suitable for itinerary planning, considering factors such as performance, accuracy, versatility, and computational efficiency.
    ○ Test each language model with a diverse range of travel scenarios, including different types of destinations, accommodations, activities, and transportation options.
    ○ Iterate and refine the language model based on user feedback and testing results, aiming to enhance its effectiveness, reliability, and user experience.
